<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Earn" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Earn,</orth> 1) ancient spelling of <emph>yearn,</emph> q. v.<lb />2) a) to acquire as a reward or wages: <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 115</bibl> (sth. of a p.). <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 278</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 46</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 13</bibl>.
<lb />b) to deserve: <cit><quote>his excellence did e. it, ere he had it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 99</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I and my sword will e. our chronicle,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 175</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>feast the army; we have store to do't, and they have --ed the waste,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 16</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>